						               													<description>In this game developed in conjunction with the Municipality of Villa Mar&amp;iacute;a, the player must tour the city, passing through various educational and cultural institutions, and various points of interest, in order to get learning points, which will crown him as the winner of the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It can be played from 2 to 4 participants representing a group of visitors. It consists of a three-day tour of different places that the city offers to know and learn. At the end of the journey, whoever makes the most enriching trip wins, but the idea is that &amp;ldquo;everyone has learned interesting things&amp;rdquo;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Learning Points&amp;quot; can be earned in various ways during the game. The die indicates the number of movement points on the board and the number of squares that must advance on the timer. Thus, it moves around the board that represents the map of the city.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This game has the particularity of being accompanied by an application for mobile devices with which the cards of the game are scanned to obtain more information about the places that are visited.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
